rComments: Sharon Lee is a pretty good professor. Due to the course being biology-related, the material is fairly heavy. Dr. Lee however tries to make all lectures as entertaining and easy as possible which is nice. She also provides "Study slides" for you to practice content that will be on the tests which is greatly appreciated.

(PSY 3301) Sharon has got to be one of the kindest profs I've ever been taught by. Although the grading for the paper was harder than I expected, her exams were very very straightforward and could be passed by studying the text/lec's. She has answered every single question I have ever had and did so in the kindest manner. I highly recommend her.

She is an excellent professor. Her lectures are engaging and she incorporates her own experiences and knowledge to keep things fresh. She always makes note of the important topics which makes studying easier. I get the feeling that she cares about her students and she actually enjoys teaching.

Honestly an amazing professor. Truly cares about her students and wants everyone in her class to succeed. Will offer help if necessary, and responds to emails promptly. Lectures felt engaging and showed she put effort into the class. Textbook is required for some diagrams, but that should be expected with any biology-related class.
Very great prof. Pay attention, do the study slides and you'll do great. simple as that

She is a sweet and nice professor. She cares about her students and makes stats easier. Make sure to do well on the homework because those add up to your final grades a lot. Theyre pretty easy if you follow the lectures, plus, if you understand the concepts/ hw shes always available to help.

Really sweet. It's a heavy course load, lots of info to cover and you definitely have to read the textbook, but its free online. 2 midterms, 2 assignments, final. Synchronous lectures but they're recorded. Takes a long time to get midterm/assignment grades back. I'd take her again I think.

I've taken two classes with Prof Lee now and she can be a bit dry but enjoyable. Lectures are good and easy to take notes from. The textbook was important for this class but it is available for free online. The lectures provide most of the info with the textbook as backup readings. do yourself a favour and take this prof- I was scared to take stats but could not have asked for a better prof to learn from! She genuinely cares about her students and she is so sweet it's awesome I 10/10 recommend
Awful professor. Gives review slides, but most questions had nothing to do with the review? Certainly would not take a class with her again.

She is very clear on what she is testing on. She posts study slides and sometimes the questions are taken straight from the study slides. As long as you keep up to date with the information, and study the study slides she posts, you should get a good mark.

Amazing prof. The course was super tough, but she made it enjoyable. Very helpful and willing to answer questions, and super funny and easy to talk to in-office hours. Teaching style is engaging, but her pace is a little slow. REALLY recommend her for this course!!!

Dr. Lee is a great professor. She truly cares about her students and will respond to your emails very quickly. I have had Dr. Lee for a number of classes, this class requires work but if you keep on top of the homework and readings you will succeed. Great professor, knows her stuff extremely well. If you attend class, do the homework slides and review your notes you should pass with a good grade. Mid terms and exams are not cumulative.

She really is a good prof who knows her stuff. The course is packed but interesting and she takes the time to answer questions. A very kind and intelligent professor. Some of her course material or projects are a bit tough but after finishing you will realize how helpful this knowledge will be in the future. She really wants the best for her students

She's so boring! All she does is read from her slides, which are pretty much taken directly from the textbook that we're supposed to read on our own time anyway. She doesn't even add any of her own information.
